ul.li:
B.2.4Departments can limit the use of Government of Canada electronic networks and devices or impose employment consequences if the activity or behaviour:
B.2.4.1Is unacceptable or criminal in nature;
B.2.4.2Violates Treasury Board or organizational policies and codes of conduct and other published requirements;
B.2.4.3Impacts negatively the performance of Government of Canada electronic networks and devices;
B.2.4.4Impedes organizational operations or the delivery of services; or
B.2.4.5Breaches the Duty of Loyalty requirement for public servants (i.e., does not refrain from public criticism of the Government of Canada).
